    "prose_paragraphs": [
      "Designers reach for Weathered Wood when they want a roof that disappears into 'looks correct' rather than competing for attention. It is balanced, slightly cool, and difficult to pair badly. On a Florida house with bright sun and white stucco, it is one of the safest specifications you can write.",
      "The shingle profile carries a deep shadow line that emphasizes the gray tone in midday light. At dusk the whole roof becomes one quiet plane that frames the rest of the house instead of competing with it.",
      "Difficult to pair badly. The one place it disagrees: bright primary-yellow houses, where the cool undertone fights the warm siding."
